pr_body:
(For triggering CI.)

Personal notes:

- [x] Pull BATMAN sources into ~`main`~ `batman-no-changes` branch too so I can more easily see what I've changed: see #3.
- [x] ~Should BATMAN still be using `netif_trans_update`?~ Whatever, just disabling on FreeBSD now.
- [x] Fix Mellanox Connectx-* drivers not compiling anymore.
- [x] Go though TODO's in my code.
- [x] Fix up the new fields in `struct ifnet`.
- [x] Do I really wanna go ahead with `if_fill_domain`? If so, don't forget to update the ifnet(9) manpage.
- [x] Can currently create multiple interfaces with the same name.
- [x] Update `ifconfig`.
- [x] Allow choosing routing algo (`ra`) in `ifconfig` on interface creation.
- [x] Update `ifconfig` manpage.
- [x] Add `batman_adv(4)` manpage.
- [x] Fix destroying interfaces.
- [ ] (Upstream) Be a bit more explicit about errors; a lot of things error silently (e.g. `batadv_softif_slave_add`). Generally make BATMAN a bit better about error handling (another e.g. `batadv_forw_bcast_packet_if` not propagating errors from `batadv_send_broadcast_skb`).
- [ ] Remove entry from ideas page once finished: https://wiki.freebsd.org/SummerOfCodeIdeas.
- [x] Replace GPL headers pulled from Linux.
- [x] Replace GPL code pulled from Linux (`XXX-GPL`).
- [x] Support selecting BATMAN algo with `IFLA_BATADV_ALGO_NAME`.
- [x] ~Support other attributes.~ Involves netlink generic, out of scope.
- [x] ~Replace all the places where we access `net_dev->dev_addr` directly. (Is there a better solution to this? Like can we make `LLADDR((struct sockaddr_dl *)ifp->if_addr->ifa_addr)` somehow point to `dev->dev_addr`?)~ Can now access `dev->dev_addr` directly.
- [x] Implement `pskb_may_pull` correctly and uncomment all the:

```c
/* drop packet if it has not necessary minimum size */
if (unlikely(!pskb_may_pull(skb, hdr_size)))
	return -ENODATA;
```

- [x] Bring out the big functions in `linux/netdevice.h` into ~`linux_netdevice.c`~ `linux_netdev.c` (`dev_queue_xmit`, `netif_rx`).
- [x] Understand why when we have to resolve ARP before sending packet, it takes too long and we end up sending an initial malformed packet instead.
- [ ] AFAICT [iproute2](https://github.com/shemminger/iproute2) is missing the batadv type in the help printout.
- [ ] Wireshark has few issues w.r.t. BATMAN packets.
- [ ] ~Port [`batctl`](https://github.com/open-mesh-mirror/batctl).~ Will be done in the future with: https://github.com/obiwac/batctl-gsoc/pull/1, but for now, integrate policy changes in ifconfig.
- [x] Fix `batadv_hardif_put` and uncomment usages.
- [x] Make sure bigger packets also work.
- [x] ~See what extra stuff I can enable in the makefile.~ -> Nothing ðŸ˜„ 

Example Linux usage:

```log
ip link add name bat0 type batadv:
2: bat0: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST> mtu 1500 qdisc noop state DOWN group default qlen 1000
    link/ether 6e:74:38:8e:d0:6d brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff
ip link set dev eth0 master bat0
ip addr flush dev eth0
ip link set up dev bat0:
2: bat0: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP> mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue state UNKNOWN group default qlen 1000
    link/ether 6e:74:38:8e:d0:6d brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff
    inet6 fe80::6c74:38ff:fe8e:d06d/64 scope link tentative
       valid_lft forever preferred_lft forever
ip addr add 192.168.0.1/24 dev bat0:
2: bat0: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP> mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue state UNKNOWN group default qlen 1000
    link/ether 6e:74:38:8e:d0:6d brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff
    inet 192.168.0.1/24 scope global bat0
       valid_lft forever preferred_lft forever
    inet6 fe80::6c74:38ff:fe8e:d06d/64 scope link
       valid_lft forever preferred_lft forever
```

So I can quickly copy/paste in `kgdb`:

```console
add-kld /usr/obj/usr/home/obiwac/gsoc/freebsd/amd64.amd64/sys/GSOC/modules/usr/home/obiwac/gsoc/freebsd/sys/modules/batman_adv/batman_adv.ko
```

Filter out ELP and OGM2 packets from Wireshark:

```console
not (batadv && (batadv.batman.packet_type == 3 || batadv.batman.packet_type == 4))
```

Resources:

- https://www.open-mesh.org/projects/batman-adv/wiki/Understand-your-batman-adv-network

pr_title: Code pulled from Linux with no changes
pr_body:
